[SN]TITLE[SN]
Wales full-back Matthew Morgan makes his debut as Blues edge out Bristol at Arms Park

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Cardiff Blues completed their pre-season preparation with a hard-fought 25-24 victory over Bristol.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Wales hopeful Matthew Morgan started at number 15 against his old club while No 8 Nick Williams also made his debut despite joining from Ulster in December 2015 after shoulder surgery.
Wales international Tom James and Steven Shingler both scored tries for the hosts, as did Aled Summerhill.
Gavin Henson kicked two conversions and a penalty for Bristol.
